io.sarl.lang.compiler.batch

Enum CleaningPolicy

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CleaningPolicy>
      • io.sarl.lang.compiler.batch.CleaningPolicy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<CleaningPolicy>

    public enum CleaningPolicy
extends Enum<CleaningPolicy>
    The policy that should be used for cleaning the files after a compilation.
    Since:
    0.10
    Version:
    io.sarl.maven.batchcompiler 0.12.0 20210527-171007

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      FULL_CLEANING
      All the files and the root temp directory are removed.
      INTERNAL_CLEANING
      The subfolders of the root temporary folder will be cleaning with the Files.cleanFolder(java.io.File, java.io.FileFilter, boolean, boolean) function, with no file filtering.
      NO_CLEANING
      No cleaning.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NO_CLEANING

        public static final CleaningPolicy NO_CLEANING
        No cleaning. All the files that are generated by the SARL compilation stay as they are.

      • INTERNAL_CLEANING

        public static final CleaningPolicy INTERNAL_CLEANING
        The subfolders of the root temporary folder will be cleaning with the Files.cleanFolder(java.io.File, java.io.FileFilter, boolean, boolean) function, with no file filtering.
